---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Oliver Richman — the maker behind Oliver Tate Furniture. Bespoke furniture inspired by curves in nature, built in Cleveland, Ohio."
>

  <section class="about-hero section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">The maker</span>
      <h1 class="section-heading">About</h1>
      <div class="divider"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-body section">
    <div class="container about-layout">

      <!-- Photo -->
      <div class="about-photo-wrap">
        <div class="about-photo-placeholder" aria-label="Portrait photo — coming soon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect width="300" height="400" fill="#f0ece3"/>
            <circle cx="150" cy="140" r="60" fill="#d8d0c0"/>
            <ellipse cx="150" cy="340" rx="100" ry="80" fill="#d8d0c0"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <p class="photo-caption">Oliver Richman — photo coming soon.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio -->
      <div class="about-text">
        <h2>Oliver Richman</h2>
        <p>
          I'm a furniture maker based in Cleveland, Ohio. Under the name
          <em>Oliver Tate Furniture</em>, I design and build bespoke pieces
          for clients who want something made specifically for them — furniture
          that couldn't be pulled off a showroom floor.
        </p>
        <p>
          My work is driven by a single question: what does wood want to do?
          The curve of a branch, the sweep of a river bend, the arc of a breaking
          wave — these are the forms I keep coming back to. I don't force wood
          into rigid geometry; I look for the shapes that feel inevitable, that
          could only have come from this particular piece of material.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every commission begins with a conversation about how you live, what
          the piece needs to do, and what draws you to natural forms. The design
          follows from that — drawn by hand, refined in the shop, built once
          and built right.
        </p>

        <div class="divider"></div>

        <h2>The process</h2>
        <ol class="process-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Discovery.</strong> We talk — by phone, email, or in person —
            about what you need and what you're drawn to. I ask a lot of questions.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Design.</strong> I produce hand sketches and, for complex pieces,
            a scale drawing. We refine until the form feels right, then I send a
            written proposal with a fixed price and timeline.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Build.</strong> I select the wood personally — grain, figure,
            and character matter as much as species. I send photos as the piece
            takes shape in the shop.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Delivery.</strong> I deliver and place within the Cleveland
            metro area. White-glove handling, every time.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="divider"></div>

        <h2>Materials &amp; finish</h2>
        <p>
          I work primarily in domestic hardwoods — black walnut, American cherry,
          white oak, and hard maple — sourced from local and regional mills.
          The species is chosen for the piece, not the other way around: a curved
          dining table base might call for steamed and bent white oak, while a
          writing desk might want the warmth of cherry.
        </p>
        <p>
          Finishes are hardwax oils (Rubio Monocoat, Osmo) and traditional shellac.
          Both age well, protect without obscuring the grain, and can be touched
          up in the field without stripping — important for pieces meant to last
          more than one generation.
        </p>

        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: var(--space-8);">
          Start a conversation
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.about-hero { padding-block-end: var(--space-4); }

.about-layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  gap: var(--space-12);
  align-items: start;
}

@media (min-width: 900px) {
  .about-layout { grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr; }
}

/* Photo */
.about-photo-wrap {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--space-3);
  position: sticky;
  top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-8));
}

.about-photo-placeholder {
  overflow: hidden;
  background: var(--color-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-dark);
}

.about-photo-placeholder svg {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
}

.photo-caption {
  font-size: var(--text-xs);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-style: italic;
  text-align: center;
  max-width: none;
  margin: 0;
}

/* Text */
.about-text h2 {
  font-size: var(--text-2xl);
  margin-block-end: var(--space-4);
}

.about-text p {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  margin-block-end: var(--space-5);
}

.process-list {
  list-style: none;
  counter-reset: process;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--space-5);
  padding: 0;
  margin-block-end: 0;
}

.process-list li {
  counter-increment: process;
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-4);
  align-items: baseline;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}

.process-list li::before {
  content: counter(process, decimal-leading-zero);
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: var(--text-2xl);
  color: var(--color-wood);
  opacity: 0.5;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  line-height: 1;
}
</style>
